Standalone Bastion Reporting Server Architecture

Enterprise Automated Reporting Solution with Secure Access

Architecture Overview

This solution provides a dedicated Windows Server 2022 for automated report generation and task scheduling, accessible exclusively through Azure Bastion. The architecture eliminates public IP exposure while enabling scheduled reporting workflows, email distribution, and secure remote administration.

Key Components

1. Azure Bastion Service (Standard SKU)
- Managed PaaS service with automatic updates and patching
- 99.95% SLA for production workloads
- Standard SKU enables Entra ID authentication
- Browser-based RDP access over HTTPS (port 443)
- No VPN infrastructure required

2. Windows Server 2022 VM (Reporting Server)
- Dedicated server for report generation
- Private IP address only (no public IP)
- Windows Task Scheduler for automation
- Support for multiple reporting tools
- Automatic Windows Updates enabled

3. Reporting Tools (Post-Deployment Installation)
- Power BI Report Server (modern dashboards)
- SQL Server Reporting Services (classic reports)
- PowerShell scripts (custom automation)
- Python environment (data science reports)
- Email distribution via SMTP

4. AzureBastionSubnet (Dedicated Subnet)
- Minimum /26 address space (64 IPs)
- Reserved exclusively for Bastion service
- Must be named 'AzureBastionSubnet' exactly
- Isolated from VM subnet

5. VM Subnet (Reporting Server Subnet)
- /24 address space (254 available IPs)
- Private addressing only
- Protected by Network Security Group
- VNet peering to Bastion subnet

6. Public IP Address (Bastion Only)
- Static allocation for consistent access
- Protected by Azure DDoS Protection
- Only component exposed to internet
- Standard SKU for reliability

7. Network Security Group (NSG)
- Inbound: RDP allowed only from Bastion subnet
- Outbound: HTTPS allowed for updates
- Outbound: SMTP allowed for email reports
- All other traffic denied by default

8. Optional Azure Files Storage
- 100GB SMB file share
- Report archival and retention
- Backup and disaster recovery
- Centralized file storage

Standard SKU Features

1. Entra ID (Azure AD) Authentication
- Single sign-on with corporate credentials
- Multi-factor authentication (MFA) enforcement
- Conditional access policies apply
- Eliminates shared passwords
- Complete audit trail of access

2. Native Client Tunneling
- Direct RDP from Windows Remote Desktop
- Better performance than browser access
- Full feature support (copy/paste, multiple monitors)
- Automation and scripting support

3. Secure Access Control
- Azure RBAC controls VM access
- Just-in-Time (JIT) access integration
- Session logging to Azure Monitor
- Compliance-ready audit trails

