Connection Flow

Step 1: Admin authenticates with Entra ID in Azure Portal
Step 2: Azure RBAC verifies admin has Bastion access permissions
Step 3: Admin selects reporting server VM
Step 4: TLS connection established to Bastion public IP (443/tcp)
Step 5: Bastion initiates RDP to VM private IP via VNet
Step 6: RDP traffic proxied through secure tunnel
Step 7: Session encrypted end-to-end and logged to Azure Monitor
Step 8: Admin installs reporting tools and configures tasks
Step 9: Scheduled tasks run automatically 24/7
Step 10: Reports generated and emailed to recipients

Required Network Ports

Direction      Source             Destination        Port     Purpose
Inbound        Internet           Bastion            443      Admin access (HTTPS)
Inbound        GatewayManager     Bastion            443      Control plane
Inbound        Bastion Subnet     Reporting VM       3389     RDP from Bastion
Outbound       Reporting VM       Internet           443      Windows Updates
Outbound       Reporting VM       Internet           25/587   SMTP email reports
Outbound       Reporting VM       Internet           53       DNS resolution
Outbound       Bastion            Azure Storage      443      Session logs

